Aboitiz Power, MacroAsia Corp.: Philippine Stocks Preview

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-05-02T00:47:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-02/aboitiz-power-macroasia-corp-philippine-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies may
have unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 1 percent to
4,319.51.  Aboitiz Power Corp. (AP)  : The company is “ready” to
invest in a 300-megawatt coal-fired power plant in the southern
Philippine island of Mindanao, a stock exchange filing showed.
The company is prepared to spend its own funds to speed-up the
construction of the project, it said. The stock gained 1.8
percent to 31.55 pesos.  MacroAsia Corp. (MAC)  : Lufthansa Technik Philippines
Inc., a provider of aircraft maintenance and repair services
that’s 49 percent owned by MacroAsia, will spend $30 million to
expand its facility, a stock exchange filing showed. The stock
fell 1.9 percent to 3.05 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in Manila at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net  